snippet.textDisplay: I feel like you could say one of the central themes of this pokemon season is dealing with an inferiority/imposter complex/syndrome. Both Hop and Bea have tried time and again to beat a seemingly unbeatable opponent. When they’ve failed so much that they start doubting themselves, they also begin to realise that there is more to their journey than that one opponent they’d set for themselves at the beginning.
